                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/18176</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Special
                        Agent <persName type="to">Silliman</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-05-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 18, 1916</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your May 15, 4 p.m. It is assumed <hi rend="italic">de facto</hi> Government will
                    not oppose pursuit of bandits raiding American territory while matters discussed
                    at Scott-Obregon conference are subject of negotiations between both
                    Governments. If you think Governor apt to carry out threat to oppose pursuit
                    bandits, discreetly call above to his attention.</p>
                <p>American force pursuing Glen Springs raiders into Mexican territory.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
